\nbird\" of the jail because he sang daily\nfor the prisoners, gave his last con\ncert last night when his mother,\nfather, brother, four sisters.and about\n50 other relatives called, to. say good\nbye.. At his mother's request he sang\nKipling's \"Mother O' Mine!\"\nYesterday, as he?' Wail being taketa\ntb tl^e. death cell',, he sang1 the ''.Miser\nere\" from \"II- Tcovotore.\" -jSfe\nMINNESOTA BaW CLOS^.\nSt. Paul, Mihn-.'Deci .lO.T\u2014The^ouite\nbank of Greenbush, in JRoseau courity,\nclosed its doors last night. The sus\npension of business was not. caused by\ngeneral financial conditions, accord\ning to F. E. Pearson, state superin\ntendent of banks, but becaiise of poor\nmanagement by former officers of the\nbank.. The capital is $10,000 and tho\nsurplus $8,000. Olaf Holdahl of\nIioseau is president, and A E. Hol\ndahl of Greenbush. cashier. The de\nposits are $181,000. The meeting of\nstockholders will l)e held tonight and\nan effort will be made to have the.\nbank reopened at once.\nThe situation was brought 'atyiut,\nMr. Pearson said, by the making-.of\npoor loans by the former manage\nment.\nCHIIjD not drowned.\nShanghai. Dec. 10.-\u2014Five weeks aft\ner Linda Moors, 3-year-old daughter\nof 1 Leonard Moors, had disappeared in\nthe night from a river steamer oh the\nYangtze from' Shanghai to Hankow,\nthe parents leanied that the child had\nnot been -drowned. An. anonymous\nletter was received by the father de\nirianding a ransom of .$4,000 for the\nreturn, of the child.\nMr., and Mrs. Moors with' the-.little\ngirl, a son and a nurse left Shf.ftMai\nfor Hankow on. the 8teamer WoWi|ig\non September 15. The parent*'shd\nthe son occupied one-, state room and\nthe little girl was left fh the care of\na nurse in an. adjoining state room.\nThe nurse saw the little girl the last\ntime at midnight when the boat was\nnear Chinkiang. When she awaken\ned at 6 o'clock the next morning-when,\nthe boat was neariag Nanking the\nchild had vanished Every effort to\nfr GRA